The photoconductivity response of a localized system is usually described by the Drude–Smith model (DS model) which considers a series of backscattering events36:8ΔσDSω=Nq2m*τs1−iωτs1+∑j=1∞cj1−iωτsj\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
